The paper deals with image manipulation and generation, specifically in the domain of fashion images. This suggests that it is likely to fall under the computer vision (cs.CV) and graphics (cs.GR) categories. Additionally, the use of generative adversarial networks (GANs) and attention normalization layers indicates a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the use of sketches and color strokes as input suggests a possible connection to multimedia (cs.MM).
